Daphne du Maurier proposed her for the main role in the film adaptation of her novel "My Cousin Rachel" in 1952.
The play became a worldwide success.
With her longtime friend Bette Davis, she starred in"Lullaby for a Corpse."
He married Marcus Goodrich (1946-1953), and they had a son, Benjamin.
